.SH NAME
HTMLMediaElement.durationchange_event \- HTMLMediaElement:
durationchange event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]durationchange\f[R] event is fired when the
\f[CR]duration\f[R] attribute has been updated.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
