ondurationchange = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
These examples add an event listener for the HTMLMediaElement\(cqs
\f[CR]durationchange\f[R] event, then post a message when that event
handler has reacted to the event firing.
.PP
Using \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R]:
